results.name: Number of proper divisors of n that are abundant (A005101).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
example: The proper divisors of 24 are 1, 2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12. Only one of these, 12, is abundant (in A005101), thus a(24) = 1.
The proper divisors of 120 are 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8, 10, 12, 15, 20, 24, 30, 40, 60. Six of these are abundant: 12, 20, 24, 30, 40, 60, thus a(120) = 6.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Nov 14 2017
